<p>The <code>make</code> tag creates a new item during iteration.</p>

<h2>Make Syntax</h2>
<pre>{open}items{close}
  {open}make $newField = $value * 2{close}
{open}/items{close}</pre>

<h2>Example</h2>
{data 'prices'}
  [
    {"item": "Apple", "price": 1.00},
    {"item": "Banana", "price": 0.50}
  ]
{/data}
<pre>{open}prices{close}
  {open}$item{close}: ${open}$price{close}
{open}/prices{close}</pre>
<table border="1">
  <tr><th>Item</th><th>Price</th></tr>
{prices}
  <tr><td>{$item}</td><td>${$price}</td></tr>
{/prices}
</table>

<h2>Note</h2>
<p>The make tag allows creating computed fields during data iteration.</p>
